    {
      "id": "K1suh1vr8NyIZvV9N3fS1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2121.2598922125817,
      "y": 8272.776573961251,
      "width": 1166,
      "height": 300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bGX",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 817571997,
      "version": 1131,
      "versionNonce": 1038705949,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775230706263,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Now even to classify and predict and majorly when we talk about working with images or heavy data\nlike videos and all there is another subset that we have inside Machine Learning whihc is called \nas Deep Learning(DL).\n\nDL more works with Neural network.\nin Machine Learning we are taking decisions on certain factors, when we increase the size of these factors\nand after increasing the size we make it pass through multiple layer, like not compare with one image but\nmultiple image, not compare with one kind of image but multiple kind of image, and such multiple layers\nwhere in layers are generating and layers are interacting then it becomes Deep Learning. So not a simple\nmodel but a rigourous model where in communication first happen in one layer then next layer, layers keep\non getting smaller but result is more precise and slowly we get result. this is what Deep learning is \nabout. So layer by layer extraction and then precising our result. that is what is Deep Learning.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Now even to classify and predict and majorly when we talk about working with images or heavy data\nlike videos and all there is another subset that we have inside Machine Learning whihc is called \nas Deep Learning(DL).\n\nDL more works with Neural network.\nin Machine Learning we are taking decisions on certain factors, when we increase the size of these factors\nand after increasing the size we make it pass through multiple layer, like not compare with one image but\nmultiple image, not compare with one kind of image but multiple kind of image, and such multiple layers\nwhere in layers are generating and layers are interacting then it becomes Deep Learning. So not a simple\nmodel but a rigourous model where in communication first happen in one layer then next layer, layers keep\non getting smaller but result is more precise and slowly we get result. this is what Deep learning is \nabout. So layer by layer extraction and then precising our result. that is what is Deep Learning.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
