    {
      "id": "GXZa6-RccuIPlqR91GM4G",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2122.0255172125817,
      "y": 9921.944542711251,
      "width": 1232,
      "height": 600,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bHM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 800040477,
      "version": 2648,
      "versionNonce": 536807101,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775237169275,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Speccially in terms of vectors. So lets say point is lie in middle of the cube. then communication can go\nup, down, front, back, digonal so it can be a N directional communication. So these kind of communication\nto find their pattern, like where this communication, which direction it can move to find a pattern how to\nmake it efficiently move Like if we have to find a related data in table it is very simple rowwise or\ncolumnwise but it 3D it can be in direction. SO for this moving and finding a relation, finding a pattern\nmathemetician they came with a formula with vectors. which allowed us to create vector databases. Now\nit can make more sence because when we can find patterns, when we can find relations then it make more\nsence to store those vectors and we started storing data into vector databases. New kind of database whihc\nis specialized for vectors. Which allowed us to communicate with any kind of language.\nFor example -> It allowed us to create \n    If Hi Rahul! is written\n        Hi Amit! is written\n    then I know that after Hi there can be a person's name after this there can be ! mark so we can predict\nthis now. Prediction is already a function of Machine Learning which is inside this because we can do\nall these things there came another subset of Deep learning which is LLM.\nthis we have learn due to , the thing with LLM is it can only still deal with text.\nFor example -> If we ask a long syntax or If we make a long conversation with LLM that I am working on a\n database which is about lets say animals and there are entries of cow and I want to fetch all the entries\nof cow. Now from this it will pickup the words, It will understand that we need a SQL query, It will get the\ntable name animals and it will see what what column and everything. then it will give us a query. But at the\nend of the day we are getting a SQL query. We still get a text, so at best what our LLM can do is that our\nLLM can give us text. But based on the text that we receive and text specifically can be the code or the command\nor the anything whatever code or command we receive that is at the end is text that we now need to give to \na tool.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Speccially in terms of vectors. So lets say point is lie in middle of the cube. then communication can go\nup, down, front, back, digonal so it can be a N directional communication. So these kind of communication\nto find their pattern, like where this communication, which direction it can move to find a pattern how to\nmake it efficiently move Like if we have to find a related data in table it is very simple rowwise or\ncolumnwise but it 3D it can be in direction. SO for this moving and finding a relation, finding a pattern\nmathemetician they came with a formula with vectors. which allowed us to create vector databases. Now\nit can make more sence because when we can find patterns, when we can find relations then it make more\nsence to store those vectors and we started storing data into vector databases. New kind of database whihc\nis specialized for vectors. Which allowed us to communicate with any kind of language.\nFor example -> It allowed us to create \n    If Hi Rahul! is written\n        Hi Amit! is written\n    then I know that after Hi there can be a person's name after this there can be ! mark so we can predict\nthis now. Prediction is already a function of Machine Learning which is inside this because we can do\nall these things there came another subset of Deep learning which is LLM.\nthis we have learn due to , the thing with LLM is it can only still deal with text.\nFor example -> If we ask a long syntax or If we make a long conversation with LLM that I am working on a\n database which is about lets say animals and there are entries of cow and I want to fetch all the entries\nof cow. Now from this it will pickup the words, It will understand that we need a SQL query, It will get the\ntable name animals and it will see what what column and everything. then it will give us a query. But at the\nend of the day we are getting a SQL query. We still get a text, so at best what our LLM can do is that our\nLLM can give us text. But based on the text that we receive and text specifically can be the code or the command\nor the anything whatever code or command we receive that is at the end is text that we now need to give to \na tool.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "JyazT3zc7a0KL7tHwa-bu",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2137.9317672125817,
      "y": 10583.221886461251,
      "width": 176,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bHN",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 87047037,
      "version": 21,
      "versionNonce": 597005149,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775237188577,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What is Tool? ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What is Tool? ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "zUzJzhym7kyGwmDgNW6tN",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2189.1895797125817,
      "y": 10627.350792711251,
      "width": 1188,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bHO",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1254367261,
      "version": 867,
      "versionNonce": 319024179,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775237525935,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "tool can be anything that performs a action.\nExample -> when we say it summarizes a book, So to summarize we need to execute some code or summarizing\nit still a whole textual thing. But when we say it runs DB query or it calculate somedata based on something\nfor us, It performs an action of 2+3, which means in the background there is calculator.\n\nSo whenever a LLM query or LLM result goes to a tool and tool performs certain actions, those actions\nintegrated with our LLM model which means we are talking to a model, model gives command to a tool and now\ntool performs a action then it is called as agent.\nSo agent is LLM + tool, which means making our LLM output actionable.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "tool can be anything that performs a action.\nExample -> when we say it summarizes a book, So to summarize we need to execute some code or summarizing\nit still a whole textual thing. But when we say it runs DB query or it calculate somedata based on something\nfor us, It performs an action of 2+3, which means in the background there is calculator.\n\nSo whenever a LLM query or LLM result goes to a tool and tool performs certain actions, those actions\nintegrated with our LLM model which means we are talking to a model, model gives command to a tool and now\ntool performs a action then it is called as agent.\nSo agent is LLM + tool, which means making our LLM output actionable.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "D02jCcSqj0rF716ESP3Ax",
      "type": "text",
