    {
      "id": "p6u3YJZlkw9C4qMcy0cGI",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2216.1075484625817,
      "y": 12893.964073961251,
      "width": 1243,
      "height": 825,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bHW",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1745464164,
      "version": 2537,
      "versionNonce": 2146475100,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775581275583,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In LLMs we are giving prompt, those prompt are also given in certain kind of file which is MD(MarkDown) file and \nall the attacks are happening in MD files.\n\nSo try to build a tool(this tool will help us to get understanding of LLM and understanding of different\nterminologies related to LLMs), What is the tool that we have to build?\n\nCreate a git repo of MD files. Now out of these MD files there are 3 type of files which is\n    Actionable 98%\n    Non Actionable 100%\n    Wrong Action(threat) 30% -> it can detect the threat on my MD file, it will identify the threat\n            Others which are not threat, it will mark them as safe and safe also with percentage\n            like actionable is 98% sure that it is safe, Non actionable 100% safe, Sometimes \n            non actionable can be a threat also.\n    NOn Actinable (threat) 60% safe hence this is also a threat for us.\n\n30% -> severity level is High\n60 % -> medium\n\nOne way is our LLM is detecting that it is a threat by LLM\nanother way is we ourself are saying that if this word is written, if this item is written on or if this\nkind of action is happening, consider it is a threat Even if LLM is not considering a threat, we consider\nit is a threat this is called as Rule based learning where in we are setting a rule like if this is \ncoming then this is a threat, and all these kind of threat detection, whenever the code is pushed in\ngit, whenever PR is made, IN main branch of git we have one code, we already have some MD file in the\nmain branch. Now developer from another branch make changes in the MD file and then they try to merge.\nSo whenever they try to merge first our action get triggered whihc means whatever analyzer we are \nbuilding this analyzer should be triggered and this analyzer will tell us this merge is safe or not.\nIf the merging is safe, it will perform the merging, If merging is not safe it will tell us merging\nPR is not safe because of this this reason.\n\nSupermemory -> is trying to do somethign like this build by 22 age people in Dec 2025\n    now 40 million dollar valuation.\n    ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In LLMs we are giving prompt, those prompt are also given in certain kind of file which is MD(MarkDown) file and \nall the attacks are happening in MD files.\n\nSo try to build a tool(this tool will help us to get understanding of LLM and understanding of different\nterminologies related to LLMs), What is the tool that we have to build?\n\nCreate a git repo of MD files. Now out of these MD files there are 3 type of files which is\n    Actionable 98%\n    Non Actionable 100%\n    Wrong Action(threat) 30% -> it can detect the threat on my MD file, it will identify the threat\n            Others which are not threat, it will mark them as safe and safe also with percentage\n            like actionable is 98% sure that it is safe, Non actionable 100% safe, Sometimes \n            non actionable can be a threat also.\n    NOn Actinable (threat) 60% safe hence this is also a threat for us.\n\n30% -> severity level is High\n60 % -> medium\n\nOne way is our LLM is detecting that it is a threat by LLM\nanother way is we ourself are saying that if this word is written, if this item is written on or if this\nkind of action is happening, consider it is a threat Even if LLM is not considering a threat, we consider\nit is a threat this is called as Rule based learning where in we are setting a rule like if this is \ncoming then this is a threat, and all these kind of threat detection, whenever the code is pushed in\ngit, whenever PR is made, IN main branch of git we have one code, we already have some MD file in the\nmain branch. Now developer from another branch make changes in the MD file and then they try to merge.\nSo whenever they try to merge first our action get triggered whihc means whatever analyzer we are \nbuilding this analyzer should be triggered and this analyzer will tell us this merge is safe or not.\nIf the merging is safe, it will perform the merging, If merging is not safe it will tell us merging\nPR is not safe because of this this reason.\n\nSupermemory -> is trying to do somethign like this build by 22 age people in Dec 2025\n    now 40 million dollar valuation.\n    ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
